Emoni was born as the daughter of a powerful noble. She
inherited her mother's beautiful appearance and her father's
competitive personality. She had a happy childhood, being
loved by her two older brothers despite the age difference.

Emoni, who has grown up, begins to admire her active and
successful older brothers. The eldest son who competes on
equal terms with cunning aristocrats despite his young age.
The second son who possesses exceptional business acumen
despite his frail health.

For Emoni, her two older brothers were her pride and heroes.
However, her father did not expect her to achieve the same
success as her brothers. He believed that marrying into a
good family was the happiest thing for her.

Emoni still wished to succeed like her brothers. Her father
relented and gave her three chances, but Emoni failed each
time. While she had some success, her failures were due to
arrogance and recklessness.

Emoni's father saw through her recklessness and gave her
three chances. However, Emoni attributed her failures to the
environment rather than herself. She believed that it was
society's fault for not allowing women to succeed.

Emoni decided to leave home in order to impress her admired
brothers and prove her stubborn father wrong. Although her
father noticed her departure, he did not attempt to search
for her.
